ve experienced a few higher level people leaving our guild because they have no one to group with of a similar lvl. This seems to be a fairly common problem and what that could be resolved if we could get an alliance going as described below:<br>
<br>
Perhaps we can get something similar set up on Vazaelle.<br>
<br>
Please post your thoughts here.  Thanks.<br>
<br>
Cut and pasted from everlore.com -<br>
<br>
Greetings,<br>
<br>
I wanted to take this time out to make everyone aware of the Druzzil Ro Alliance. What is the Druzzil Ro Alliance? The Druzzil Ro Alliance is a collection of Guilds on the Druzzil Ro Server that have formed together for the purpose of doing high level dungeons, planes, and dragons, without having the necessity of being in a high level guild. With such an alliance all the participating guilds remain in their present guild and are never forced to lose their guild tag. This way they are not forced into giving up their home or their friendships with those they have grown to know and love, and still get to play the game...on their own terms.<br>
<br>
Their is now an option for those that want to be involved in the high level end of the game. No longer will people be forced to be in a guild with people they do not care to associate with on a daily basis. Now people will have the option of remaining within the confines of their guild and doing said raids and staying in their home without ever losing their guild tag. When raids are conducted no guild will ever demand any guild member from the alliance ever to disband from their guild for the purpose of the raid. All those in the raid remain tagged into their guild for the conductivity of the raid. No one ever loses their guild tag under any conditions where it corresponds to the Druzzil Ro Alliance and its operations with regards to raiding.<br>
<br>
The Druzzil Ro Alliance has also come up with some base policies such as looting and simply working together as a team. The later will force guild leaders to be guild leaders and help to keep relations friendly between guilds. Not everyone will see eye to eye one hundred percent of the time, but that does not mean we can not be civil and respectable and try our best to bring about an honest and honorable resolve to whatever the situation may be.<br>
<br>
In short the Druzzil Ro Alliance is in it for fun. We pay monthly fees a month to have fun, so fun we shall have, and what better way to do it then with our friends.<br>
<br>
If you are a respective guild leader and interested in joining the Druzzil Ro Alliance please visit the forums at www.druzzilroalliance.cjb.net and read the looting rules under the General Discussion forums. If you agree with these rules then please leave a post in the General Discussion forums requesting to join and you shall be prompty added to the Druzzil Ro Alliance.<br>
<br>
Please make sure you leave your website URL if applicable in the post so we may add it as a link. This way anyone interested in being in a guild apart of the alliance will have an easier time in chosing a guild in which they can call their home.<br>
<br>
If you have a greivance with an alliance member and wish to enter your guild into the alliance please leave said greivance at the door upon entering. No one will hold anything upon any other alliance members. The past is simply the past and this is a new beginning for us all. As well, no one will be refused admittance into the alliance as well...so long as they agree to the loot rules. We shall endeavor in all things to enjoy our company, and our fellowship, and the game we have come to know as EverQuest. Here it is an even playing field, and for us involved it shall be our fun and our enjoyment of the game. To those of you who may be joining you are welcomed with open arms. May the gods and godesses bless you in the days ahead, and may the hunting begin.<br>
<br>
Sincerely Yours,<br>
Banegrivm Shadowblight<br>
Sovereign Lord of the 1st Fist of Light<br>
Member of the Druzzil Ro Alliance - www.druzzilroalliance.cjb.net<br>
