<br>
A few months ago, Oshkos resigned as GL and handed it over to me.  At the time we had quite a few peeps 45+ who were (are) good friends and a whole stack more who were 20-45.<br>
<br>
When Osh resigned the vast majority of the higher levels also left.<br>
<br>
If we had not been in the Alliance, I believe that right now Wardens would have collapsed.  I knew nothing about leading a guild - heh, still learning - but through bugging the heck out of the other GLs (mostly River <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) we have pulled through and are now in a position to again be the guild the original members intended for us to be.<br>
<br>
&lt;end Wardens sob&gt;<br>
<br>
Recently, the Alliance grew from 6 o 9 guilds.  Current guilds are now: Razor's edge, Wardens, Walkers, Lucid Chimera, Sacred Circle of Life, Jinxed, Shadow's End, Epic Shadows and Unbroken Circle of Valor.<br>
<br>
So far as I am aware, while there are guilds who have spoken to River about joining the Alliance, until all the current guilds are comfortable with each other, there will be a pause on admittance of new guilds.<br>
<br>
